        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "5. money—\"thirty pieces of silver\" (Mt 26:15); thirty shekels, the fine payable for man- or maid-servant accidentally killed (Ex 21:32), and equal to between four and five pounds of our money—\"a goodly price that I was priced at of them\" (Zec 11:13). (See on [1719]Joh 19:16.)",
        "children": []
      }
